 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Assistant General Counsel American Medical Association 78 reviews Chicago, IL 60611 American Medical Association 78 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Assistant General Counsel 
 Chicago, IL or Washington, D.C 
The American Medical Association (AMA) is the nation's largest professional Association of physicians and a non-profit organization. We are a unifying voice and powerful ally for America's physicians, the patients they care for, and the promise of a healthier nation. To be part of the AMA is to be part of our Mission to promote the art and science of medicine and the betterment of public health. 
 
We continuously work to embed equity in our internal practices and are committed to increasing the diversity of our staff across all levels of the organization. We intentionally work to create the right conditions to enable our employees to feel that they can be their authentic selves and fully participate in the life of the enterprise. 
 
We encourage and support professional development for our employees, and we are dedicated to social responsibility. We invite you to learn more about us and we look forward to getting to know you. 
 
We have an opportunity at our corporate offices in Chicago or Washington, D.C for an Assistant General Counsel on our Office of General Counsel team. As an Assistant General Counsel you will serve as legal counsel and proactive partner to AMA business units as assigned; provide counsel to managers on legal matters impacting managers' areas of responsibility. You will also prepare supporting legal documents, including appropriate agreements and related documentation. You will analyze legislation, regulations, court decisions of interest to the AMA, and maintain subject matter expertise and conduct highly complex work critical to the AMA. 
RESPONSIBILITIES: 
Counsel on Digital Initiatives, Emerging Technology and Data 
Serve as legal counsel to assigned AMA business units, by providing objective, thorough, timely and well-researched legal advice to management on complex legal issues 
Negotiate, draft and finalize contracts supporting the AMA’s mission-related and revenue-generating activities, with emphasis on AMA digital and data privacy initiatives, including digital/social marketing and engagement, ad products, ad-tech, insights, mobile applications, digital health, interoperability and information blocking, data licenses, personal data collection activities (US and international), HIPAA-compliant activities, telemedicine, precision medicine, artificial/augmented intelligence (AI), machine learning, software as a medical device (SaMD), big data and data analytics, fraud and abuse/reimbursement, wearables and the Internet of Things (IoT) 
Assist management’s assessment of legal and business risk of various courses of action to support AMA initiatives, policies and procedures 
Provide guidance to stakeholders on legal, privacy, data protection and other applicable compliance requirements 
Provide counsel and transactional solutions to management and employees on a variety of legal questions related to general corporate issues, strategic relationships and regulatory compliance 
Review, analyze, interpret and disseminate new laws and regulations affecting nonprofit organizations and AMA initiatives, and aid in implementing any required changes 
Other Business Agreements and Regulatory 
Draft and review a wide variety of business agreements and related documents 
Not for Profit Matters 
Review, analyze, interpret and disseminate new laws and regulations affecting nonprofit organizations and AMA initiatives, and aid in implementing any required changes. 
Complete regulatory communications and filings 
May include other responsibilities as assigned
 REQUIREMENTS: 
J.D. from an accredited leading law school 
Licensed to practice law in Illinois or Washington, DC 
Minimum 8-10 years of relevant experience, with experience in digital health, data privacy, and emerging technologies; exposure to both a law firm and a corporate environment preferred, significant breadth and depth of matters 
Experience in effectively collaborating in cross-functional business and legal teams to address and resolve legal issues to achieve the desired business units’ outcome 
Knowledge of laws and regulations applicable to AMA and its business units and initiatives, including U.S. data protection laws 
Certified Information Privacy Professional certification (CIPP) preferred, but not required. 
Outstanding analytical and critical thinking skills with a focus on practical outcomes 
Superior interpersonal skills including demonstrated ability to interact well with clients to gain their respect and confidence to build a trusting relationship 
Excellent verbal and written communication skills with an ability to persuade and communicate confidently 
Excellent research skills 
The ability to think creatively and where applicable the ability to present multiple solutions with varying degrees of risk to a given legal problem and to succinctly explain each solution and the corresponding risk mitigation the solution provides 
Demonstrated ability to perform with limited supervision; must be confident in independent judgment 
Some travel required 
The American Medical Association is located at 330 N. Wabash Avenue, Chicago, IL 60611 and is convenient to all public transportation in Chicago. It is located near Union Station and the Capitol in Washington, D.C.
 We are an equal opportunity employer, committed to diversity in our workforce. All qualified applicants will receive consideration for employment. As an EOE/AA employer, the American Medical Association will not discriminate in its employment practices due to an applicant’s race, color, religion, sex, age, national origin, sexual orientation, gender identity and veteran or disability status. 
